text: Arizona's 10th Legislative District is one of 30 in the state, located entirely in Pima County. As of 2018 there are 49 precincts in the district, with a total registered voter population of 117,650. ==Political representation== The district is represented for the 2019-2021 Legislative Session in the State Senate by David Bradley (D, Tucson) and in the House of Representatives by Kirsten Engel (D) and Domingo DeGrazia (D). ==References== Category:Pima County, Arizona Category:Arizona legislative districts
title: Arizona's 10th legislative district
